      "personal": {
        "legalName": "",
        "height": "",
        "weight": "",
        "age": "",
        "aliases": "",
        "gender": "",
        "description": "You are a master of machines, commanding a stable of drones that can handle everything from stealthy infiltration to front-line combat. With an experienced mechanic's touch, you fine-tune your gear until it runs better than anything off the shelf. Your drones can operate independently with deadly precision, thanks to advanced AI and customized loadouts. But when it's time to take the wheel, you don't hesitate to jack in. Your control rig melds mind to machine, letting you 'become' the vehicle. Your honed reflexes can let you speed through oncoming traffic or veer over the side of an on-ramp to fly through the air and land smoothly on the ground, leaving your pursuit in the dust. Whether you're leading the charge or making the getaway, you and your machines move as one.\n\nKeep in mind, your drones are more than capable of operating on their own. The one exception is high-speed chases - when you need a fast getaway, you should 'jump into' your van with your control rig to drive, as you're much better than the autopilot. Otherwise, you don't need to jump into your drones. Just give them commands, and they'll be effective - whether it's your battle drones gunning down enemies or your spy drones sneaking into a facility to scout around."
      },
